event_tag.name: Navigate: Exploring College and Careers
event_tag.description:
Allows students to:

  • examine various careers and educational requirements;
  • evaluate different educational opportunities after high school;
  • identify academic choices and extracurricular activities that will enhance their applications;
  • research the cost of post secondary education;
  • explore types of financial aid and educational assistance;
  • imagine their own path to success.

This resource is an introduction to the investigation of careers and college and is designed for young students. Many students and their families may not be familiar with the pathways to education after high school, and Navigate provides information to begin preparing for success.

Provided by the Financial Literacy Coalition of Central Texas.

event_tag.name: ASL Interpreter Provided
event_tag.description:
An ASL interpreter will be provided for these programs.

The City of Austin is committed to compliance with the Americans with Disabilities Act. Reasonable modifications and equal access to communications will be provided upon request. For assistance please call 512-974-7449.

event_tag.name: Asian American & Pacific Islander Heritage Month
Make the Most of Your Medicare Benefit
event_tag.description:
With Lee Green

The Austin Public Library invites you to an educational presentation by licensed insurance agent Lee Green, who specializes in helping Medicare beneficiaries navigate their coverage options. He will be presenting programs in February, June and October at Pleasant Hill, Howson and Manchaca branches, covering topics such as:

  • How do I sign up for Medicare?
  • What does it cost?
  • What are Parts A, B, C, and D of the federal Medicare program?
  • What’s the difference between a Medicare supplement and a Medicare Advantage plan?

event_tag.description: Corwin Levi’s book Mirror Mirrored provides the framework for his mixed-media exhibit featuring local, national and international artists reimagining Grimms’ Fairy Tales.

2nd Wednesday of the month at 6:30 PM

event_tag.name: Community Health Education Workshops
event_tag.description:
oin HealthStart Foundation at the fourth of our six Community Health Education Workshops (CHEWS). In this workshop children will learn tell what body parts make up the circulatory system, what this system does, and what foods feed their circulatory system. Children will participate in activities that help their blood and lymph flow through the body. Children will learn through stories, songs, hands-on activities, and creation of a snack that feeds and strengthens their circulatory system.

Space is limited so preregistration is required. Children may register for more than one week. PREREGISTER HERE or at the Central Library Children’s Desk.

September 18 Your Brain - The Control Center

September 25 Your Brain - A Healthy Start

October 2 Your Blood Factory - Inside the Bones

October 9 Your Circulatory System - Go with the Flow

October 16 All Kinds of Muscles

October 23 Digestion - The Beginning and the End

Sponsored by the Austin Public Library and the HealthStart Foundation

event_tag.name: Mesoamerican Celebration
event_tag.description: A cultural program about the indigenous people of Mesoamerica—Aztecs, Mayan, and others.  Have fun through stories, shadow show puppetry and arts and crafts.

event_tag.name: Using the Three-Act Structure to Plot Your Novel or Screenplay
Chinese Mandarin-English Storytime
event_tag.description: This all-ages storytime uses both Chinese Mandarin and English to present books, rhymes, finger-plays, and songs. Materials are not necessarily translated. The storytime flows naturally using both languages, allowing children to feel comfortable in a multilingual environment. No prior experience with Chinese is necessary to participate in.

event_tag.name: College Planning Workshops
event_tag.description: Join Access College America's Dale Price, MBA for a free college planning workshop series. This series of 4 programs is designed for an information packed hour to help you learn how to best assist your child while navigating through the college admission process like a pro.

event_tag.name: Safe Space
event_tag.description: Discuss what’s important to you in a safe setting. Group is led by a licensed clinical social worker. Everyone is welcome, especially those experiencing homelessness, but space is limited. Topics include: how to build self-esteem; anger management; how to resolve conflict; grief and loss; health and mental health, etc.

event_tag.name: Talk Green to Me
event_tag.description: Talk Green to Me: Sustainable Living Series features workshops and discussions about sustainable communities, co-existence with nature and small footprint living. The program also emphasizes that shared Library resources are intrinsically green.

event_tag.name: Track Your Family Tree
event_tag.description: Are you interested in learning more about your family history and tracing your lineage? This monthly genealogy program is for you!

event_tag.name: National Small Business Week
event_tag.description: The City of Austin’s Small Business Program presents this series of educational events to help Austin’s small businesses and those who wish to start a small business. Attendees will receive free advice on subjects including: funding, marketing, legal, and business planning from fellow business owners and experts in their respective fields. Visit SmallBizAustin.org to register.

event_tag.name: Tech Connect
event_tag.description: Tech Connect is a week of programs aimed at introducing people of all ages and walks of life to new digital technology and skills.

event_tag.name: Yarn Craft Club
event_tag.description: Do you want to learn some new knitting and crocheting techniques? Or work on your yarn project with other yarn lovers in a casual setting?

event_tag.name: Día de los Niños
event_tag.description: Día de los Niños is a nationally recognized initiative that emphasizes the importance of literacy for all children from all backgrounds. It is a daily commitment to linking children and their families to diverse books, languages and cultures.

event_tag.name: Girls Who Code
event_tag.description: Girls Who Code is a national non-profit organization working to close the gender gap in technology and change the image of what a programmer looks like and does. Their programs inspire, educate, and equip young women with the computing skills to pursue 21st century opportunities.

event_tag.name: Traditional Healing
event_tag.description: Taught by Marika Alvarado

event_tag.name: Women's History Month
event_tag.description: Women's History Month highlights the contributions of women to events in history and contemporary society. It is celebrated in March.

event_tag.name: Talking Pictures
event_tag.description: Join us as we watch and discuss films of various genres.

event_tag.name: Open Book Austin

event_tag.description: African American History Month or Black History Month celebrates the people and events in the history of the African diaspora.

event_tag.name: Podclub
event_tag.description: Have you ever listened to an amazing podcast and wanted to talk about it with someone afterwards? The Podclub is like a Book Club for podcasts. Listen to the story, then come to the Library to discuss it with people in your community.

event_tag.name: Board with Books
event_tag.description:
Do you love playing board games? Then come to Board with Books!

¿Le encantan los juegos de mesa? ¡Venga a Board with Books!

A wide range of modern and traditional board games are available to play. Come and learn something new or bring a personal favorite and teach someone else how to play!

Ofrecemos una gran variedad de juegos de mesas – ambos modernos y tradicionales – para su gusto. ¡Venga a jugar y aprenda algo nuevo o traiga un juego favorito y enseñe cómo jugar a otra persona!

event_tag.name: Guided Healing Meditation
event_tag.description: What is a Guided Healing Meditation? It's an opportunity to relax, unwind, integrate and let go of everything that is limiting realization of our highest potential.

event_tag.name: Ben Franklin Circle
event_tag.description:
Ben Franklin Circles are a national conversation movement committed to encouraging participants to ask two big questions: How can we improve ourselves? How can we improve our world?

This civic dialogue program will work towards answering these questions together using Ben Franklin's 13 Virtues as we explore how to live a good life and be a good citizen.

event_tag.name: Introduction to Basic Python
event_tag.description: An introduction to basic Python. This class instructs participants in the fundamentals of the Python programming language.

event_tag.name: Library Commission
event_tag.description:
The Library Commission makes recommendations to the city council on matters relating to the establishment, maintenance and operation of the Austin Public Library.

For more information visit austintexas.gov/librarycommission.

event_tag.name: Walk & Talk Book Club
event_tag.description:
Join us for a walking book club. We will gather at the Library and take our meeting outside to walk as we discuss the book selection of the month. All adults are welcome, whether you have read the book or not.

Second Wednesdays, 11 AM - 12 Noon

event_tag.name: Read It Sing It Let Us Hear It Open Mic
event_tag.description:
You bring the talent, we provide the mic and PA. Creatives, from beginner to advanced, are invited to share music, poetry, comedy, improv, theater and performance art.

All ages welcome. Sign-up starting at noon the day of open mic. There are nine 15-minute slots with 5 minutes between. First come, first served. Performances must be appropriate for a Library setting.

For more information, contact the Carver Branch at 512-974-1010 or join our Facebook Group.

event_tag.name: Early Childhood Special Needs Playgroup
event_tag.description:
This playgroup is an opportunity for caregivers and their children with special needs to play and socialize with other, same-aged children in a safe space. The playgroup will practice gross motor, fine motor, speech and language as well as cognitive and adaptive developmental skills. Toys and materials are provided.

Spanish speaking families are welcome! Siblings and therapists are also encouraged to join in and participate.

event_tag.name: Money Matters
event_tag.description: Come learn about financial topics like borrowing, credit, financial recovery and home ownership from the Financial Literacy Coalition of Central Texas.

event_tag.name: Ukulele Club
event_tag.description: Learn simple chords and songs in a welcoming environment.

event_tag.name: Early Literacy Playgroup
event_tag.description: Playing is learning! Play is a great way to help develop and reinforce early literacy skills. This come-and-go program is designed to give caregivers and their children time to explore together. Toys, board books, and a weekly craft will be provided.

event_tag.name: Yoga Storytime
event_tag.description:
Practice your mindfulness, hear a story, and learn more about yoga. No mat is required. / Practique como mantenerse enfocado, escuche un cuento, y aprenda más sobre la práctica de Yoga. No necesita traer un tapete para yoga.

Programs begin on time, for best experience we recommend you do too! Please arrive a few minutes early to gain entrance. Note that in some locations, free tickets (available in the branch on the day of the program) will be required for admittance. Contact individual branches to arrange group visits of 5 or more children to storytimes.

event_tag.name: Powered Libraries
event_tag.description: Ideas Powered: It’s What We Do seeks to broaden the awareness of library services to the public and provide resources to librarians working in the state in order to promote libraries as vital, technology-centered institutions in the community.

event_tag.name: Romance Book Club
event_tag.description: Join us to discuss romance novels, classic romances, Young Adult romance and more!

event_tag.name: Water Forward Summer Series
event_tag.description:
Austin Water is collaborating with the Austin Public Library, other city departments, a Citizen Task Force and the community to develop a water plan for the next century. The 100-year plan will recommend strategies to best manage Austin’s water supply now and in the future.

Learn more and get involved with the Water Forward Summer Series of events.

And what’s the summer without water and popsicles? Please enjoy a cool treat at every location. Children’s activities will be available. Must be accompanied by an adult. 

For more information about Water Forward and to sign up for the electronic newsletter, visit www.austintexas.gov/waterforward.

event_tag.name: Medicare and Medicaid
event_tag.description: Questions about Medicare and Medicaid? Get answers at "Medicare Made Clear," presented in English and Spanish. Presented by Benjamin Brown-Grave.

event_tag.name: ACT vs SAT
event_tag.description: The Austin Public Library invites you to this series about the ACT and SAT. Come find out which one is right for you or your high school student.

event_tag.name: Screenwriting
event_tag.description:
Want to learn how to write for the screen?
Well, cut to the chase and visit the Manchaca Branch of the Austin Public Library to learn from independent filmmaker Joseph Bowman. He has had three scripts produced in the last year and has shown his work at SXSW and the Hill Country Film Festival.

event_tag.name: Tealightful Speaking with You
event_tag.description: Come to the Library for a cup of tea and pleasant conversation.

event_tag.name: Bilingual Adult Coloring Time

Venga a liberarse del estrés mientras disfruta de los beneficios relajantes que tiene el colorar el segundo miércoles de junio a agosto. Todos los materiales serán provistos.

event_tag.description: Tell a five minute story – truth, fiction, funny, serious, read or memorized, any story about life, fantasy or yourself. New themes each time!

event_tag.name: Adult Hoppy Hour
event_tag.description:
Let your work week stress melt away at this special, extra cute, after-hours Hoppy Hour!

Adults 18+ can kick back and make extra cute crafts or snuggle up to some of the cutest low-allergy animals in Austin at the Austin Public Library!

Tiny Tails to You will bring their sweet adorable petting zoo with over 25 animals for you to meet and cuddle while artist Rita Wang will teach you to sculpt itty bitty clay cacti complete with tiny terracotta pots! 

Hand sanitizer and mats (for guests worried about their clothing) are included.

event_tag.name: Senior Series
event_tag.description:
Milwood is the place for seniors to gather, have fun and create.
We have something for everyone!

event_tag.name: Camp Bluebonnet
event_tag.description: We’re Celebrating the Texas Bluebonnet Award by reading books from this year’s list! Remember you’ve got to read 5 to decide and after attending these programs you’ll be well on your way to be qualified to vote next school year! Join us to enjoy a variety of books and related activities.

event_tag.name: Kids Summer Film Fest
event_tag.description: The Austin Public Library is your place for free movie fun this summer!

event_tag.name: Audiobook Club
event_tag.description:
Read It, Hear It, Love It.

Come and enjoy the audiobook club at University Hills. Audiobooks provide an additional dimension to books. It’s a great feeling to have a voice guiding you through the story effortlessly, making the book all the more magical, particularly when you hear the author’s own voice. Plus, you can even pick up some techniques for any reading aloud you might do yourself.

event_tag.name: Puppet Happy Hour
event_tag.description: Bring your puppets, share your skills, solve your puppetry problems, try out a skit or just talk puppets with other puppet nerds at this monthly event. We'll have a mic and table for your use as needed.

event_tag.name: Money Smart Week
event_tag.description: Come work on your financial literacy and become money smart!

event_tag.name: Trivia Night
event_tag.description:
Join friends and fans for trivia fun at the Library!

With 8 rounds of 8 questions, bring a team of up to 6 members for question/answer, fill-in-the-blank, audio & video rounds.

Snacks provided.

Recommended for adults.

event_tag.name: Juntos Online
event_tag.description:
The whole family is invited to an afternoon of online fun!

Win prizes and learn to use different internet resources on your computer or smartphone.

event_tag.name: APL Volumes
event_tag.description:
Download or stream archived live radio shows and podcasts all about your local Austin Public Library system. There's bonus podcast content that includes interviews with creatives and interesting Austinites. 

Volumes won a 2017 Texas Library Association Branding Iron Award. Join our APL Volumes Facebook Group for weekly updates facebook.com/groups/APLvolumes.

event_tag.name: Express Yourself
event_tag.description:
The Austin Public Library welcomes the whole family to participate in eight weeks of FREE workshops to explore media and technology to express yourself.

Recommended for ages 8 and up.

Exprésate a través de medios sociales y tecnología

event_tag.name: Read Watch Talk
event_tag.description: Literature purists will stand by the book. Film buffs will make a case for the movie. Either way, there is something to discuss. Take part in our movie-book club by reading on your own and/or watching with us, and then discussing the merits of each following the film.

event_tag.name: Tabletop Tuesday
event_tag.description:
Roll the dice, deal the cards and spin to win at Tabletop Tuesday! The entire 3rd floor of the Central Library is open for gaming, and patrons of all ages can explore a variety of games, new and old.

In the Children's Area, enjoy classic titles and educational games for the whole family. In the Teen Area, open up epic co-op adventures or try hilarious party games.

Patrons of all ages are welcome to enjoy games from the Teen Area collection in the library's 3rd floor Atrium!

event_tag.name: Clases de Yoga y Meditación
event_tag.description:
Learn how to manage pain and stress with natural alternatives — YOGA and Meditation! Free Yoga Classes and Meditations led by certified instructors from PureAction.org and the Heartfulness.org.

¡Aprenda cómo manejar el dolor y el estrés con alternativas naturales como lo son la YOGA y la meditación! Estas clases gratuitas son dirigidas por instructores certificados de PureAction.org y Heartfulness.org.

event_tag.name: Yoga Meditation Classes
event_tag.description: Learn how to manage stress through yoga and guided meditation techniques.

event_tag.name: Austin Out Loud
event_tag.description: This new series at Old Quarry Branch brings local writers into the Library to read from their work. Recommended for ages 17 and up.

event_tag.name: Keep Calm and Color On
event_tag.description: Coloring is great for relaxation; coffee is a great way to start your day. Come and join us for a colorful, stress-free morning and wake up at your own pace.

event_tag.name: One-Stop Assistance
event_tag.description:
My Library Keeps Me Healthy invites you to drop in during One-Stop Assistance office hours: 

  • Talk to a social work student
  • Get computer help 
  • Visit a nurse for health screenings

event_tag.name: East Austin Studio Tour
event_tag.description:
The East Austin Studio Tour (EAST) is a free, annual, self-guided art event, providing the public an opportunity to meet local artists and artisans.

The tour takes place the second and third weekends in November. To highlight EAST, the Austin Public Library is showcasing ten artists at select East Austin Branch Libraries.

event_tag.name: Facebook Live
event_tag.description: Get a live look of Austin Public Library collections and services on Facebook. The Library broadcasts from its Facebook page @AustinLibrary (unless noted otherwise) and completed episodes are automatically archived in the page’s videos tab for leisurely viewing.

event_tag.name: Power Up at Your Library Day
event_tag.description: Join the Austin Public Library for Power Up at Your Library Day, the state-wide celebration of the innovation and engaging events happening in Libraries across Texas on Thursday, September 15, 2016. Watch this short video to learn more.

event_tag.name: Board Games
event_tag.description: Join us for playing a variety of board games.

event_tag.name: Monstober
event_tag.description: Monsters, movies, manga and more! Robots, Frankenfigures, horror galore! Skeletons, stop-motion and even socks, we’ll explore! Visit various participating branches to get the full Monstober experience!

event_tag.name: Japanese-English Storytime
event_tag.description:
This is a dual language storytime for children aged 5 and under and their caregivers, featuring stories, songs, fingerplays, rhymes, and other pre-literacy skill building activities in both English and Japanese.

Some material is presented in English while other material is presented in Japanese, allowing for a natural transition between stories and activities and exposing children to both languages in an inviting environment. Storytime lasts about 30 minutes.

event_tag.name: Clay Club
event_tag.description: Join us for a hands-on clay experience, and – while you're at the Library – explore our diverse collection of DIY books!

event_tag.name: Coloring Book Time: Art as Meditation
NaNoWriMo
event_tag.description:
Write Your New Novel
November is National Novel Writing Month, and the New Central Library is here to support writers in their novel-writing endeavors. This event is a collaboration between the Austin Public Library and the Library Foundation.

event_tag.name: Writing
event_tag.description: The Austin Public Library invites you to a series of workshops that will teach you the basics of writing for various genres and purposes.

event_tag.name: Keep Austin Wild
event_tag.description: Come learn how to peacefully co-exist with coyotes in Austin, and things you can do to stop them from coming into human spaces, and also how to safely eliminate possibilities for pet or human contact. Presented by Kristen Eastman, Wildlife Educator, Austin Animal Center.

event_tag.name: Music & Movement
event_tag.description:
Bring your favorite little one to stretch, sing, dance & explore music with rhythm instruments! Program length can vary. Focuses on the Sing and Play recommendations for early literacy which helps develops gross motor skills, listening skills, and social skills, while introducing new vocabulary.

Programs begin on time, for best experience we recommend you do too! Please arrive a few minutes early to gain entrance. Note that in some locations, free tickets (available in the branch on the day of the program) will be required for admittance. Contact individual branches to arrange group visits of 5 or more children to storytimes.

event_tag.name: Summer Shorts
event_tag.description: Please join us for our short story discussion series. The group will discuss 50 Great Short Stories, edited by Milton Crane, starting with “How Beautiful with Shoes.”

event_tag.name: Juneteenth
event_tag.description: Juneteenth is a day for all Americans to celebrate African American freedom, history and culture. Also known as Emancipation Day, Juneteenth commemorates June 19, 1865, the day Union General Gordon Granger and 2,000 federal troops arrived on Galveston Island to take possession of the state of Texas and to enforce emancipation.

event_tag.name: Skill Up Workshops
event_tag.description:
Do you have the chops to write that catchy headline? Or do you have mad coding skills? Can you channel your inner Don Draper and own that pitch? If you answered no to any of these questions, then Austin Public Library has some invaluable workshops for you. And they’re free!

Master new skills in data, technology, design and marketing. Taught by instructors from General Assembly. Presented in partnership with Google Fiber Austin.

Own your future. Mark these dates on your calendar and skill up!

event_tag.name: Business Workshops
event_tag.description: Austin Public Library has many resources for starting a business, such as online databases and workshops led by business professionals.

event_tag.name: New Fiction Confab
event_tag.description: Now in its seventh year, the New Fiction Confab invites several of the most notable authors to publish new work in 2015 and 2016 to spend a day in Austin’s libraries leading writing workshops, reading their work, and engaging in conversations that offer the community a unique opportunity to explore and discuss contemporary fiction with the authors shaping America’s literary landscape. The Confab is one of the Library Foundation’s largest literary programs, spotlighting the finest fiction on bookshelves today, and the authors who bring these novels and stories to life.

event_tag.description: Local writers read their own work aloud for the public. Join the Aural Lit Facebook Group to get regular updates.

event_tag.name: Winter Cheer Celebrations
event_tag.subtitle: Holidays, Festivities and More!
event_tag.summary: Join Austin Public Library Winter Cheer Celebrations all season long. Our locations will be hosting fun events and programs all winter celebrating holidays, the changing season, the new year, and MORE! Come spread some cheer with us.
event_tag.description: Come celebrate the holidays with the Austin Public Library!

event_tag.name: Super Smash Bros Tournament
event_tag.description: Are you ready to smash? Compete in the annual Super Smash Bros. for Wii U Summer tournament. All dates are seed tournaments for the Championship finals at the Central Library on August 14. Sign-up begins 30 minutes prior to start time. The first 32 people to sign up are guaranteed a spot to play.  Controllers will be provided but you may also bring your own. Program length is approximately 2 hours.

event_tag.name: Mario Kart 8 Deluxe Tournament
event_tag.description:
Compete in the Austin Public Library’s Annual Winter Gaming Tournament.

Doors open for sign-ups 30 minutes before each tournament and the first 32 people to sign up will be assured a spot. Controllers will be provided but you may also bring your own. All dates are seed tournaments for the Grand Championship at the Central Library on January 5, 2020 at 2 PM.  Program length is approximately two hours. 

Something for the whole family! Tournament now played with Mario Kart 8 Deluxe on the SWITCH.

event_tag.name: Million Mile Month
event_tag.description:
Million Mile Month is a one-month challenge that encourages people to come together as one large virtual community with a goal of walking, running, rolling or swimming one million miles. Sign-up is required to participate online at www.millionmilemonth.org.

Events are free and open to the public.

event_tag.name: French-English Storytime
event_tag.description:
Bonjour and welcome to this très special storytime! This is a dual language storytime for children aged 5 and under and their caregivers, featuring stories, songs, fingerplays, rhymes, and other pre-literacy skill building activities in both English and Français. Join us, s'il vous plaît!

Some material is presented in English while other material is presented in French, allowing for a natural transition between stories and activities and exposing children to both languages in an inviting environment. Storytime lasts about 30 minutes.

event_tag.name: Hora de cuentos en dos idiomas
Art Smart
event_tag.description: Love Art? Let’s be Art Smart and explore different ethnic arts, art media, and techniques at this weekly family art experience for all ages and generations.

event_tag.name: FixIt Clinic
event_tag.description: Fixit Clinics are all about do-it-together, hands-on disassembly, troubleshooting and learning to repair.

event_tag.name: Pop Up Library
event_tag.description: Come visit the Library away from the Library.

event_tag.name: Español
event_tag.description:
• programas y recursos en varios idiomas
    • inglés
    • español
    • formato bilingüe
  • eventos
  • actividades
  • clases
  • gratuitas
  • para todas las edades
  • en un ambiente amigable y seguro
  • pregunte un bibliotecario 512-974-7400
  • nuestra página en español: library.austintexas.gov/es

event_tag.name: Black History Month
event_tag.description:
Celebrate Black History Month at Austin Public Library.

Check out the special exhibits celebrating Black History Month here.

event_tag.name: Yoga is Medicine
event_tag.description: Do you feel pain or stress? Learn how to manage pain and stress with a natural alternative - Yoga! Our free classes will teach you ways to breathe and stretch safely. Find out why millions of people all around the world are using yoga as a way to feel better. Presented by PURE ACTION - Yoga is Medicine.

event_tag.name: Maker Mania
event_tag.description: Meet a scientist and make something!

event_tag.name: Write Club
event_tag.description:
Join our creative writing group! Fuel your creativity with short-timed writing exercises using provided prompts. Inspire and be inspired by others! This program is suitable for adults.

This is not a class on how to write. No instruction is given.

event_tag.name: Open Mic
event_tag.description:
The Austin Public Library Hosts Open Mics at various locations. 

Join our Open Mic Facebook Group for regular updates!

event_tag.name: Felt Friends World Tour
event_tag.description: Join us each month as we sew another felt project. This program uses sharp sewing needles and so is recommended for ages 10 and up. Adults are welcome to join in the fun!

event_tag.name: Small Business Development
event_tag.description: Do you want to start a business? Learn how!

event_tag.name: My Library Keeps Me Healthy
event_tag.description: The Library offers free programs and workshops to help you improve your health and well-being throughout the year.

event_tag.name: YA For Adults Book Club
event_tag.description: Do you put the adult in YA? Then YAFA is for you! Please join us for some excellent literary conversation.

event_tag.name: Health & Wellness
event_tag.description: The Library offers free programs and workshops to help you improve your health and well-being throughout the year.

event_tag.name: Echo and the Bats
event_tag.description: Come dance along with Echo and the Bats - Austin's first All-Youth-Librarian band. We use our love for books and music to blend the two into a brand new kind of show that makes reading and rocking go hand in hand!

event_tag.name: Austin History Center
event_tag.description: The Austin History Center's rich collections and expert staff support exhibits, programs, and research by the public in our Reading Room six days per week. Watch this video to learn more.

event_tag.name: Ciudadanía
event_tag.description: Clases de ciudadanía estadounidense, en inglés.

event_tag.name: Día de los Muertos
event_tag.description:
A day of fun and laughter, and remembering our loved ones passed. Learn about this traditional holiday with this fun, engaging, cultural program through stories, music, shadow show puppetry, and arts and crafts.

Un día de risas y diversión y de recordar a nuestros queridos muertitos. Aprende sobre este día tradicional con este divertido y encantador programa cultural, por medio de cuentos, música, teatro de sombras y manualidades.

event_tag.name: Conversation Café
event_tag.description: Hungry for conversation? Drop in for open, public dialogue on a variety of topics and add to the diversity of perspectives.

event_tag.name: Bad Film Festival
event_tag.description: Do you love bad movies? Follow the Bad Film Festival Facebook Group

event_tag.name: Central Concerts
event_tag.description: Central Concerts bring musicians and the community together for free live performances at the Central Library.

event_tag.name: Introduction to the Internet and Email
event_tag.description:
This computer class covers the basics of browsers and Web sites, how to search online, the basics of setting up an email account, composing and receiving messages, managing an inbox and attaching and opening documents.

Prerequisite: Completion of Basic Computer Skills or mastery of mouse handling and keyboarding.

event_tag.name: Barking Book Buddies
event_tag.description:
Certified Austin Dog Alliance volunteer teams with trained therapy dogs will be waiting for kids to read stories to them. This program improves children’s reading and communication skills by employing a powerful method: reading to a dog. Open to children of all reading levels.

Voluntarios del “Austin Dog Alliance” estarán esperando a todos aquellos niños y niñas que quieran venir a leerles a perros entrenados. Se ha comprobado que este poderoso método ayuda a que los niños mejoren su capacidad de comunicarse con otras personas y también a que eleven su nivel de lectura.

event_tag.name: Music
event_tag.description: Practice music at your neighborhood Library.

event_tag.name: Mayor's Book Club
event_tag.description: The Mayor's Book Club is an annual citywide reading campaign to encourage a community experience through reading, discussion, and exploration of shared books. The Mayor's Book Club is presented by the Library Foundation in partnership with the City of Austin Mayor's Office and the Austin Public Library.

event_tag.name: Citizenship / Ciudadanía
event_tag.description:
Learn about the US immigration process.

Aprenda sobre el proceso de inmigración.

event_tag.name: Talk Green
event_tag.description: Talk Green to Me features events that emphasize the intrinsically green nature of the Library.

event_tag.name: StoryBook Dance Making
event_tag.description: Love music, dance or reading books? What about all three at the same time? Come together for StoryBook Dance Making with your family and create a dance based on a story’s theme. All ages, mixed-abilities and drop-ins welcome! This class is taught by artists of Dance Waterloo, an interdisciplinary dance collective in Austin.

event_tag.name: Hispanic Heritage Month
event_tag.description:
Austin Public Library celebrates Hispanic Heritage Month with rich cultural experiences that enlighten and empower our community.

La Biblioteca Pública de Austin celebra el Mes de la Hispanidad con ricas experiencias culturales que iluminan y fortalecen a nuestra comunidad.

event_tag.name: Toddler Storytime
event_tag.description:
A storytime program designed for toddlers aged 18 months to 3 years and their parents, featuring stories, songs, fingerplays, and games. Program length can vary.

Programs begin on time, for best experience we recommend you do too! Please arrive a few minutes early to gain entrance. Note that in some locations, free tickets (available in the branch on the day of the program) will be required for admittance. Contact individual branches to arrange group visits of 5 or more children to storytimes.

event_tag.name: Spanish
event_tag.description: The Austin Public Library hosts events, and provides books, movies and music, for all ages in Spanish. All Library events are free and open to the public.

event_tag.name: Sensory Storytime
event_tag.description:
Sensory Storytime features interactive books, singing, and music and will incorporate some sensory activities, like movement and bubbles. This program welcomes children of all abilities to create an inclusive environment. Please talk with presenter prior to program to if you have any questions regarding your child’s needs. Program length can vary.

Programs begin on time, for best experience we recommend you do too! Please arrive a few minutes early to gain entrance. Note that in some locations, free tickets (available in the branch on the day of the program) will be required for admittance. Contact individual branches to arrange group visits of 5 or more children to storytimes.

event_tag.name: Preschool Storytime
event_tag.description:
Storytime for preschoolers aged 3-5 and their parents featuring stories, songs, fingerplays, rhymes, and crafts. Program length can vary.

Programs begin on time, for best experience we recommend you do too! Please arrive a few minutes early to gain entrance. Note that in some locations, free tickets (available in the branch on the day of the program) will be required for admittance. Contact individual branches to arrange group visits of 5 or more children to storytimes.

event_tag.name: Pajama Storytime
event_tag.description:
Feel free to wear pajamas to this family storytime in the evening featuring stories, songs, rhymes, games, crafts, and other activities. Program length can vary.

Programs begin on time, for best experience we recommend you do too! Please arrive a few minutes early to gain entrance. Note that in some locations, free tickets (available in the branch on the day of the program) will be required for admittance. Contact individual branches to arrange group visits of 5 or more children to storytimes.

event_tag.name: Spanish-English Storytime
event_tag.description:
All ages storytime which uses both English and Spanish to present books, rhymes and songs. It differs from a traditional bilingual storytime in that some material is presented in English while other material is presented in Spanish, allowing for a natural transition between stories and activities and exposing children to both languages in an inviting environment. Program length can vary.

Esta hora del cuento es para niños y niñas desde bebitos hasta de edad escolar y para sus padres. Se presentarán libros, rimas, y canciones en inglés y en español. Difiere de un programa tradicionalmente bilingüe en que el material no va a ser traducido de un idioma al otro, sino que presentaremos algunas cosas en inglés y otras en español empapando a los niños en los dos idiomas. De esta manera ellos se sentirán cómodos usando los dos idiomas. Recomendado para niños y niñas menores de 5 años.

Programs begin on time, for best experience we recommend you do too! Please arrive a few minutes early to gain entrance. Note that in some locations, free tickets (available in the branch on the day of the program) will be required for admittance. Contact individual branches to arrange group visits of 5 or more children to storytimes.

Recomendamos que llegue a tiempo, ya que las horas de cuentos comienzan precisamente a la hora programada. Para asegurar tener asiento, por favor llegue unos cuantos minutos antes del comienzo. En algunos locales se requiere tener boleto para entrar (lo puede obtener gratuitamente el mimso día del programa en la sucursal). Llame a la sucursal para hacer arreglos para traer grupos de 5 niños o más a la hora de cuentos.

event_tag.name: Cuddle Up and Read
event_tag.description:
Please join us for a special lap-sit storytime designed for our youngest library users, ages 0-12 months. Together, we will sing, chant, read and play, helping parents incorporate early childhood literacy practices into their daily life.

Program length can vary.

Programs begin on time, for best experience we recommend you do too! Please arrive a few minutes early to gain entrance. Note that in some locations, free tickets (available in the branch on the day of the program) will be required for admittance. Contact individual branches to arrange group visits of 5 or more children to storytimes.

event_tag.name: Books and Babies
event_tag.description:
A lapsit storytime program especially for non-walking babies 0-18 months and their caregivers.  Very short stories are interspersed with songs, rhymes, and fingerplays for babies and parents.  A brief playtime follows. Program length can vary.

Programs begin on time, for best experience we recommend you do too! Please arrive a few minutes early to gain entrance. Note that in some locations, free tickets (available in the branch on the day of the program) will be required for admittance. Contact individual branches to arrange group visits of 5 or more children to storytimes.

event_tag.name: All Ages Storytime
event_tag.description:
Storytime for children aged 5 and under and their parents, featuring stories, songs, fingerplays, rhymes, and crafts or other extension activities. Program length can vary.

Programs begin on time, for best experience we recommend you do too! Please arrive a few minutes early to gain entrance. Note that in some locations, free tickets (available in the branch on the day of the program) will be required for admittance. Contact individual branches to arrange group visits of 5 or more children to storytimes.

event_tag.name: Storytimes
event_tag.description:
Storytime programs introduce young children to books, rhymes, music and other fun activities. Austin Public Library offers programs matched to the typical attention spans and developmental levels of different ages of children.

Los programas de Cuentos introducen a los niños a libros, rimas, música y otras actividades divertidas. La Biblioteca Pública de Austin ofrece programas que coinciden con los niveles de desarrollo y la capacidad de atención típica de niños de diferentes edades.

La mayoría de los programas se presentarán en inglés, pero pueden ser disfrutados por personas que hablan otras lenguas.

event_tag.name: Making & Crafting
event_tag.description: Join us for making and crafting and, while you're at the Library, explore our diverse collection of DIY books!

event_tag.name: Bizaid Business Orientation
event_tag.description: BizAid Orientation provides a general overview on how to open a small business or re-imagine an existing one. Learn how to find assistance at the idea, start-up and existing stages of your business. We will cover key questions entrepreneurs should ask as well as how to find answers and business solutions. BizAid Orientation is free and open to the public, but space is limited so you must register.

event_tag.name: Programs & Workshops
event_tag.description: Library programs and workshops reflect the creative endeavors and diverse interests of the Austin community.

event_tag.name: Minecraft
event_tag.description: Join us for Minecraft free play! Laptops are available. You can also bring your own or other mobile device that has Minecraft downloaded!

event_tag.name: Book Sales
event_tag.description:
Join us for a special book sale! Proceeds from book sales directly benefit the Austin Public Library. Want to support the Library with more book sales? Visit Recycled Reads during their operating hours or check out their online storefront.

$2.00 Adult hardcover books

$1.00 Adult paperback books

$0.50 Children's books (picture books through Young Adult) 

$1.00 DVD/CDs

event_tag.name: Made With Code
event_tag.description: Made with Code is a Google initiative to get all young people interested in coding and to celebrate creativity through fun projects. Families are invited to come and give coding a try!

event_tag.name: Storytelling
event_tag.description: Listen and share in the joy of storytelling!

event_tag.name: Movies
event_tag.description: Join us for a movie screening. Watch and discover new films at the Austin Public Library.

event_tag.name: Literature Live!
event_tag.description: A Latin-American legend about why the cuckoo bird lays its eggs in other bird's nests. Literature Live! brings literature to life through puppetry, storytelling, song, and movement.

event_tag.name: Talk Time
event_tag.description:
Improve your English conversation. ¡Mejore su conversación en inglés!

Talk Time is a program for English conversation practice with other English language learners and English speaking volunteers. No registration is necessary. The program is open to any adult who speaks some English and wants an informal and safe place to practice with others.

Participe en Talk Time: Hablemos Inglés, un programa gratis de La Biblioteca Pública de Austin, donde usted puede venir a conversar en inglés y así practicar y sentirse más seguro. No es necesario registrarse. Este programa se ofrece a cualquier adulto que hable algo de inglés y que quiera practicarlo con otros en un lugar informal y sin presiones.

event_tag.name: ¡Qué me cuentas!
event_tag.description: Practice and learn Spanish as a second language with ¡Qué me cuentas! Through reading and discussion of Latin-American short stories and newspapers, this group offers a unique way to practice Spanish for more advanced speakers. 40% proficiency in Spanish is preferred.

event_tag.name: Practiquemos Español
event_tag.description: Practiquemos Español is not a Spanish class, but rather a place to fine-tune your Spanish in a relaxed environment under the guidance of a Spanish-speaking facilitator. Participants will need to know a little Spanish to participate.

event_tag.name: Language Practice
event_tag.description: Need to practice English or Spanish? Our Language Practice sessions can help!

event_tag.name: Chess Club
event_tag.description: Learn to play chess! Children under 10 must be accompanied by an adult.

event_tag.name: Controversy & Conversation
event_tag.description:
A series of documentaries about the most controversial issues of the day. Screenings are followed by moderated discussion. Refreshments are served prior to the film and seating begins at 6 PM.

In partnership with the UT Austin Humanities Institute.

event_tag.name: Tech Time
event_tag.description:
Learn to download books and use digital Library resources. Bring in your tablet, smartphone or eReader for help navigating the Virtual Library and Overdrive, downloading eBooks, audiobooks, digital magazines and more! Tech Time sessions take place at various Austin Public Library locations throughout town. Drop in anytime during the session. The estimated setup time for each device is about 20 minutes.

Android tablets • Android smartphones • Apple iPads • Apple iPhones • Amazon Kindles • Kobo eReaders • NOOK® eReaders • Windows 10

event_tag.name: Introduction to Microsoft Word
event_tag.description:
This class introduces the tasks of word processing using Microsoft Office Word software. Students will learn to create, format, save and print a document. Students will also learn the difference between save and save as. Also covers tasks such as text justification, font and formatting, inserting an image, hyperlinking and creating a document from templates. This class is for people who have little or no experience using Microsoft Office Word.

Prerequisite: Completion of Basic Computer Skills or mastery of mouse handling and keyboarding.

event_tag.name: Introduction to Microsoft Excel
event_tag.description: This class introduces the basics of spreadsheets using Microsoft Office Excel software. Students will learn to enter, edit, copy, delete and move data; format numbers and text; change, insert, delete and sort columns and rows. It is perfect for people who have little or no experience using Microsoft Office Excel.

event_tag.name: Computer and Job Searching Lab
event_tag.description: Get help with your job search and/or bring your questions about basic computer skills including how to use the internet, email, and Microsoft Word and related topics. No prerequisites.

event_tag.name: Computación Basica
event_tag.description: Aprenda todo lo que necesita saber para comenzar a usar una computadora, desde cómo usar el ratón y el teclado, para una introducción de la internet.

event_tag.name: Basic Computer Skills
event_tag.description: Learn everything you need to know to start using a computer, from how to use a mouse and keyboard to an introduction to the internet. No prerequisites.

event_tag.name: Computers & Technology
event_tag.description: Drop in for free computer training at several Library locations throughout town. Our classes cover topics such as how to use email, look for a job, put finishing touches on your résumé and navigate social media.

event_tag.name: Teen Book Club
event_tag.description: A monthy informal book discussion for avid teen readers.

event_tag.name: NBTween Book Club
event_tag.description: A monthly informal book discussion for avid tween readers and their interested adults. Programs begin on time, for best experience we recommend you do too! Program length is approximately 1 hour. Recommended for ages 8-12 and their adults.

event_tag.name: Mother - Daughter Book Club
event_tag.description: Bring your mom and discuss what you're reading with the group. Programs begin on time, for best experience we recommend you do too! Program length is approximately 1.5 hours.

event_tag.name: Graphic Novel Book Club
event_tag.description: The Graphic Novel Book Club is an adult book club that meets monthly to discuss graphic novels and comics. Whether you’re new to the genre or are a long-time comic-lover you’re sure to find interesting conversation and a chance to read something new!

event_tag.name: Book Circle
event_tag.description: Settle in for a story or two and some hands-on activities. Programs begin on time, for best experience we recommend you do too! Program length is approximately 1 hour.

event_tag.name: Café au Lit
event_tag.description: Can't wait to tell someone about the great book you just read, or don't know what to read next? Come to a different kind of book club where you can read what you like and find out what others are reading at the same time. Join us for coffee, conversation and companionship. It's a great way to get recommendations for trying new genres and authors. It's also a great venue for telling people about that book you just finished that you want EVERYBODY to read!

event_tag.name: Steeped in Books
event_tag.description: Drop in for informal talk and tea to share your thoughts about what you're reading. Don't know what to read? Here's a perfect opportunity to pick up a few recommendations.

event_tag.name: Meet the Author
event_tag.description: Meet the Author events provide an opportunity to hear a writer read their work aloud and discuss it with an audience.

event_tag.name: Night Crafters
event_tag.description:
Are you a crafter? Do you wish you were a crafter? We’ll focus on a different craft every month; we’ll learn the basics, we’ll learn the ins and outs, and then we’ll let loose. Come learn with us!

Recommended for ages 17 and up.

event_tag.name: Crafternoon
event_tag.description: Drop by the library and make a craft while you search for books, movies and music. We've got paper crafts, easy sewing and more fun projects for the whole family. We provide the supplies; you provide the creativity. Program length is approximately 1 hour.

event_tag.name: Lego Lab
event_tag.description: With Legos, you can build anything you can imagine and tell any story you can dream up. Come to the Lego Lab to hear, see, make, and create different stories, all while building with Legos provided by the Library! Program length can vary, please call branch for details.
